-- Credit Agricole Hires Five People for Asia Fixed-Income Team in Hong Kong
-- Katrina Nicholas
-- 2010-06-28T02:07:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/credit-agricole-hires-6-for-asia-fixed-income-trading-sales-in-hong-kong.html

          
          
             Credit Agricole Corporate and
Investment Bank added to its fixed-income markets sales and
trading area, appointing five people to its Asia ex-Japan team.  
 Yue Wu is head of foreign exchange sales based in Hong Kong
and joins from Barclays Plc while Sanjay Tanna is head of Asia
energy trading, also based in Hong Kong and previously from
Petro-Diamond Risk Management Ltd. in London.  
 Damian Rowe has joined from Citigroup Inc. as head of
credit trading, debt and credit markets for Asia outside of
Japan, and Calvin Cheung has joined from Standard Chartered Plc
as director of financial institutions sales for Hong Kong.  
 Tim Haley is senior foreign exchange spot trader for Asia,
also based in Hong Kong, and he joins from Royal Bank of Canada.  
          
          


  


        